cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with resource allocation in D2D enabled cellular networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory and signal processing, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The scheduling framework proposed in the paper involves optimization and control, which are related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. Finally, the paper discusses the issue of collision reduction, which is related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
